definition.value: Whiteleg shrimp (Litopenaeus vannamei, formerly Penaeus vannamei), is a variety of prawn of the eastern Pacific Ocean commonly caught or farmed for food.
Farfantepenaeus aztecus is a species of marine penaeid shrimps found around the east coast of the USA and Mexico
*Artemisia pontica*, the Roman wormwood or small absinthe, is an herb used in the production of absinthe and vermouth. [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artemisia_pontica]
